  "markup": "\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPurpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To support employees in fulfilling their civic duty as a juror by providing time off in accordance with applicable federal, state, and local laws.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022list-style-type: none;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENotification Procedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E If you receive a summons for jury duty, you must notify your immediate supervisor and Human Resources as soon as possible after receiving the summons. You must provide a copy of the official jury summons to Human Resources upon request.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuration and Pay:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Neumo will provide paid leave for the duration of actual jury service as required by applicable state or local law. If no specific state or local law mandates paid jury duty leave, the leave will be unpaid, but employees may elect to use available Paid Time Off (PTO) to cover the absence. If you are released from jury duty early on a scheduled workday, you are expected to report to work for the remainder of your shift, unless otherwise instructed by your supervisor.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReturn to Work:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Upon completion of jury service, you must provide your supervisor with a certificate of jury service or other official documentation confirming your attendance. You are expected to return to work on your next regularly scheduled workday following your release from jury duty, unless otherwise excused.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo Retaliation:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Neumo prohibits any form of retaliation against an employee for serving on a jury.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo Contract Implied:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E This policy does not alter the \u0022at-will\u0022 nature of employment.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E"
}]]></Value>
